bodyEn:
To: The Merchant at VPA {VPA_PAYEE}

Subject: Friendly one-page — UPI paid Rs. {AMOUNT} but goods/services not delivered (UTR {UTR}; {TXN_DATE})

Madam / Sir,

1. I am {USER_NAME} (contact {MOBILE_NO}). My UPI txn Rs. {AMOUNT} (UTR {UTR}; {TXN_DATE}) to your VPA {VPA_PAYEE} is recorded on my bank account. The goods / services I contracted for have not been delivered.

2. Please deliver the goods / services within seven (7) days of receipt of this note, or refund Rs. {AMOUNT} to my VPA {VPA} via a reverse-UPI transaction. The remaining transaction slip is attached.

3. If I do not hear from you within seven (7) days, I will file a chargeback under BRDC 2018 Schedule § 7 (Non-delivery) at my bank {BANK_NAME}, and then escalate to NPCI and the RBI Ombudsman under RB-IOS 2026.

4. This communication is in good faith. I look forward to your resolution.

Place: {PLACE}
Date: {TODAY_DATE}

Yours sincerely,
{USER_NAME}
